Hero_Accursed.txt_intro: Accursed is a defensive support hero that specializes at team-fight sustain by removing stuns and debuffs off allies with fire shield, as well as healing them with cauterize.

Hero_Adrenaline.txt_intro: Adrenaline is a front-line initiator that likes to build strength and stat items to enhance his Shard Blast and Rush damage. Use your Death's Halo to control and setup team-fights for your team!

Hero_Aluna.txt_intro: Aluna is a support hero that can also be played as a semi-carry with the right items. Keep close attention to the entire map as her Power Throw(s) become global when used alongside Emerald Red.

Hero_Andromeda.txt_intro: Andromeda is a defensive support hero that also works well as an early game roamer. Amplify team-damage and scout for enemies with Aurora. Void Rip to save your carry or displace an isolated enemy.

Hero_Apex.txt_intro: Apex is a team-fight initiator or counter-initiator best played in a solo lane. He has great mobility from both Decimate and Fire Surge, alongside a large AOE stun from Armageddon to control fights.

Hero_Arachna.txt_intro: Arachna is a carry/ganker style hero that excels in 1v1 situations.  This hero lacks a strong farming tool, therefore relies on aggressive play and kills for gold, be active!

Hero_Armadon.txt_intro: Armadon is a front-line tank hero with semi-carry capabilities. His entire game plan revolves around being up in the face of enemies using Spine Burst and absorbing damage with Armadillo.

Hero_Artesia.txt_intro: Artesia is a unique support capable of dealing large magic damage or healing allies with Arcane Missles. Position behind teammates to maximize heals and damage from afar as a long-range spellcaster.

Hero_Artillery.txt_intro: Artillery is a fragile ranged carry that excels at dealing massive amounts of damage from far away. Obtaining mana regen and high DPS items will allow you to strike down foes from afar.

Hero_BabaYaga.txt_intro: Wretched Hag is a semi-carry with high mobility typically played mid or offlane. She is a great split-pusher and teamfighter with Bat Blast. Item build varies based on the situation.

Hero_Behemoth.txt_intro: Behemoth is a roamer/initiator hero most commonly played in the long-lane. Fissure can be used to block creeps and obtain lane-control. When it's no longer safe to get exp. help your team with ganks.

Hero_Bephelgor.txt_intro: Balphagore is a pushing hero that loves to teamfight as much as possible. Build tanky items and sit in the front-line gaining charges on your ultimate to devastate the opposing team.

Hero_Berzerker.txt_intro: Berzerker is a hard-carry that excels at chasing down single enemies with Chain Spike and Mark for Death. Acquire health boosting items with attack speed to deal high physical damage quickly.

Hero_Blitz.txt_intro: Blitz is a very mobile support hero that actively looks to setup kills whenever he can. Play aggressive and speed up allies when they are in danger.

Hero_Bombardier.txt_intro: Bombardier is a great solo laner with heavy nuking power able to flash farm quickly. Acquiring a staff of the master makes Air Strike a global ganking threat as well as a strong teamfight presence.

Hero_Bubbles.txt_intro: Bubbles in an initiator that controls team-fights with Song of the Sea and Kelp Field, while avoiding damage using Shell Surf and Take Cover. Kite enemies with low cool-downs and avoid damage.

Hero_Bushwack.txt_intro: Bushwack is a carry hero that excels at high mobility, constantly shifting around with Side Step, while slowing enemies. Soloing Kongor is possible with lifesteal and enough attack speed.

Hero_Calamity.txt_intro: Calamity is a semi-carry style that prefers to lane mid to take advantage of her strong 1v1 ability with Dragon's Path. Build mobility and survivability to sustain in team-fights.

Hero_Chi.txt_intro: Qi is a semi-support, anti-carry style hero that does his best to disrupt the opposing carry in team-fights. A well-timed disarm and Ancestral Assault can be devastating for the enemy carry.

Hero_Chipper.txt_intro: The Chipper is a ganker played as a main or secondary support hero using Rockets to burst down foes and stack jungle camps. Use focus buffer to protect allies from heavy magic damage spells in fights.

Hero_Chronos.txt_intro: Chronos is a carry hero with a large team-fight ultimate that allows him to lock down heroes of his choosing and focus them down. Look for kills with your ultimate, but farm is the key to his success.

Hero_Circe.txt_intro: Circle is a support hero that transforms into a farmed enemy hero of your choice. Use her  cloning power to deceive enemies and create illusions of teammates to split push lanes and cause disruption.

Hero_CorruptedDisciple.txt_intro: Corrupted Disciple is a carry hero that builds tanky and mobility items to chase down the opposing damage dealer with his Corrupted Conduit. The more you drain, the stronger you become!

Hero_Cthulhuphant.txt_intro: Cthulhuphant is a tanky frontline hero that is best played in the longlane as a solo or with in a duo manup lane. Building strength-based items increases your passive allowing you to reflect damage.

Hero_Dampeer.txt_intro: Dampeer is a carry hero revolving around constantly using spells to nuke enemies while healing up. He is great at turning team-fights from low-hp with burst heals. Build items to support your spells.

Hero_Deadlift.txt_intro: Deadlift is a pushing/team-fighting based hero that has the unique ability to resurrect fallen teammates with his ultimate. Take down enemy towers early game, while building team items for later on.

Hero_Deadwood.txt_intro: Deadwood is a ganker hero that's very flexible in his role, played most commonly in solo mid or in the offlane, either alone or with an ally. Look to use willowmaker on the enemy key target in fights.

Hero_Defiler.txt_intro: Defiler is a pushing/team-fighting hero most commonly played as a solo mid laner. Building mobility and survivability will help you deal large amounts of damage over a prolonged team-fight.

Hero_Devourer.txt_intro: Devourer is a ganker that can be played solo mid or as a longlane roamer. Use veiled rots often to land hooks and setup ganks with teammates. Item builds vary based on what position you decide on.

Hero_DiseasedRider.txt_intro: Plague Rider is an offlane hero that can achieve lane control by using Extinguish on your lane creeps, which also denies the enemy carry farm. Stack ancients and use Plague Carrier on them early game.

Hero_DoctorRepulsor.txt_intro: Doctor Repulsor is a ganker/semi-carry hero typically played solo mid or shortlane carry that can also transition to the jungle early on. With Icon, smoke to find kills to make presence on the map.

Hero_Dreadknight.txt_intro: Lord Salforis is a tanky frontline hero that is great in 1vs1 melee matchups, as well as jungling stacks quickly. Focus the enemy carry/key target with The Undying and sit in the front line in fights.

Hero_DrunkenMaster.txt_intro: Drunken Master is a mobile strength hero played in mid or offlane. Build tanky items to front-line and initiate fights while sustaining and dealing huge bursts of damage with your ultimate. Drink!

Hero_DwarfMagi.txt_intro: Blacksmith is a roamer/support hero that amplifies magic damage with flaming hammer. Boost allies with Frenzy throughout the game and use veiled rots to setup ganks. Multicast for heavy damage!

Hero_Ebulus.txt_intro: Slither is a teamfight/pusher hero that can be played as a secondary support or a solo laner. Build items based around your spells and to sustain for constant pushes with Toxin Wards.

Hero_Electrician.txt_intro: Electrician is a tanky frontline hero played in a solo lane or in an aggressive duo lane. Initiate fights with grip to hold key targets and soak damage. Level W + E if laning solo, max Q on duo lane.

Hero_Ellonia.txt_intro: Ellonia is a magic damage nuker that spams abilities from far away and slows down the enemy team. This hero excels as a solo mid or in an aggressive duo lane due to her incredible damage output.

Hero_EmeraldWarden.txt_intro: Emerald Warden is a semi-carry/utility style hero best played in an aggressive duo lane. Traps and wolves provide excellent scouting tools and control for small engagements.

Hero_Empath.txt_intro: Empath is a hard-support hero that pairs well with physical damage hard carries as she buffs them up with her As One. Build items depending on what your carry needs to thrive as you will be AS ONE.

Hero_Engineer.txt_intro: Engineer is a support hero that pairs well with another hero with a stun or a slow. He can deal great amounts of burst damage alongside a powerful team-fighting ultimate that can perplex enemies.

Hero_Fade.txt_intro: Fayde is a secondary supportive hero that typically goes offlane with another hero. Roam the map constantly and setup ganks with teammates to pick off enemies 1 by 1 using the vision from reflection.

Hero_Fairy.txt_intro: Nymphora is an all-around support hero that can be played both offensively and defensively. Mana allies and turn fights with Volatile Pod. Global gank with allies using Teleport and ward offensively.

Hero_FlameDragon.txt_intro: Draconis is a semi-carry typically played as a jungler that is great at taking triple stacks early, but soaks alot of farm. TP to towers  to aid teammates for counter-ganks and build tanky!

Hero_FlintBeastwood.txt_intro: Flint Beastwood is a long-range carry that can lane in both the mid and short farming lane. Build between boosting your ability damage or overall right-click damage based on what the team needs.

Hero_Flux.txt_intro: Flux is a front-line strength initiator hero that is great for setting up fights. Pair him together with allies that have AOE abilities to maximize his pulling mechanics on your opponents positioning!

Hero_ForsakenArcher.txt_intro: Forsaken Archer is a hard-carry played in the short-lane that transitions into the jungle to utilize her Split Fire for efficient farming. Look to teamfight with spells early, but farm when necessary.

Hero_Frosty.txt_intro: Glacius is a support hero that provides slows and freezes for your team as well as a global mana regen and mana pool aura. Acquire a Portal Key and Staff of the master to boost your ultimate later on.

Hero_Gauntlet.txt_intro: Gauntlet is an initiator/ganker hero that excels in 1v1 situations but also works well in an aggressive duo lane. Grapple to displace enemies and veiled rot to gank as often as possible!

Hero_Gemini.txt_intro: Gemini is a carry hero played in the short lane that's able to be in 2 places at once with each dog gaining full XP.  Split farm early on and look to be active and gank later with items. Build stats!

Hero_Geomancer.txt_intro: Geomancer is a support hero, long or short lane, that transitions into a roamer with his Dig and Geo Stalk. Play aggressive, setup kills and scout for your teammates where the enemies are positioned!

Hero_Gladiator.txt_intro: The Gladiator can be played in a variety of roles, most commonly solo mid and duo longlane. Showdown can be used to lineup Call to Arms and Pitfall Combinations. Acquire damage for Flagellation.

Hero_Goldenveil.txt_intro: Goldenveil is a support hero/ganker that  suits well for the offlane either in a solo or aggressive duo lane. Perch to scout for enemies in the surrounding area and land kills against isolated foes.

Hero_Grinex.txt_intro: Grinex is a ganker with high physical damage output played in the offlane or in a solo lane. Landing auto-attacks between ability casts will proc Nether Strike attacks yielding the most damage.

Hero_Gunblade.txt_intro: Gunblade is a ganker/semi-carry played in either mid or short lane farming. Due to a weakness in farming capability, it is essential to play active and look for kills whenever possible.

Hero_Hammerstorm.txt_intro: Hammerstorm is a strength carry with a built-in cleave that hits very hard with brute strength. Building sustain with attack speed and mobility is the key to success with this heavy-hitter.

Hero_Hantumon.txt_intro: Night Hound is a carry that can be played either as a shortlane farmer or in the offlane due to his ability to roam the map undetected. Build into agility items to backstab hard.

Hero_HellDemon.txt_intro: Soul Reaper is a semi-carry healer that loves to teamfight and be in the middle of the fight. He excels in 1v1 matchups and can flash farm lanes and jungle quickly. SR is great against tanky foes!

Hero_Hellbringer.txt_intro: Hellbringer is an initiatior/counter-initiator played in mid lane or as a secondary support. Summon Malphas to control fights and push towers. Acquire SoTM + Resto Stone to maximize your ultimate.

Hero_Hiro.txt_intro: Swiftblade is a hard carry played in the shortlane that is great against heavy magic damage lineups thanks to Blade Frenzy's magic immunity. Use Swift Slashes on the enemy key hero in teamfights.

Hero_Hunter.txt_intro: Blood Hunter is a strong ganker hero with low cooldowns that transitions into a carry later in the game. Gank when your ultimate is off cooldown and use tablet when enemies try to teleport away.

Hero_Hydromancer.txt_intro: Myrmidon is a support hero that is best paired with a line-stunning initiator or a carry with lockdown. Acquiring a staff of the master can transition from a support into a semi-carry style build.

Hero_Ichor.txt_intro: Ichor is a strength support that uses Transfusion to take debuffs off an ally and absorb damage taken protecting them. Front-line fights with Bloodrush and allies to sustain health over time.

Hero_Javaras.txt_intro: Magebane is an anti-magic vanguard & semi-carry for his team throughout the game. After you reach level 2, force favourable trades by blinking onto enemy heroes and burning their mana.

Hero_Jereziah.txt_intro: Jeraziah is a semi-carry that can also be played as a secondary support. He prefers to play in a solo lane for experience, also works in a dual lane. Build carry or team items based on the situation.

Hero_Kane.txt_intro: Kane is a ganker/anti-carry hero that excels mid lane or in a duo offlane. Initiate fights and lock down the enemy key hero with Face Off. Transition to a semi-carry with battle items later on.

Hero_Kenisis.txt_intro: Kinesis is a support hero with the unique ability to steal any 1st skill from an enemy player with Thoughtsteal. Use telekinetic Control to gain lane position early and deal magic burst later on.

Hero_KingKlout.txt_intro: King Klout is a ganker hero typically played in a 1vs1 lane due to his lane harassment with Goblin Toss. Initiate and counter-initiate teamfights with Parade of Power from anywhere on the map!

Hero_Klanx.txt_intro: Klanx is a hard carry hero that deals both magic and physical damage. Build mobility and survivability with damage to be successful. Stay in excellent position and poke enemies from afar with H.A.W.K.

Hero_Kraken.txt_intro: Kraken is a mid/offlane initiatior that relys on a Portal Key to land Tsunami Charge + Release the Kraken! Later look to get Shrunken Head with Stormspirit and Resto Stone to enhance initiations.

Hero_Krixi.txt_intro: Moon Queen is a hard carry that can hit up to 5 enemies with Multi-Strike bouncing. Farm core items before fighting and Moon Finale to control teamfights.

Hero_Kunas.txt_intro: Thunderbringer is a heavy nuker played midlane or as a secondary support that scales due to Lightning Rod. Lightning Storm is global to assist allies while Blast of Lightning reveals stealth units.

Hero_Legionnaire.txt_intro: Legionnaire is a fast jungler if left untouched, max W + E and farm until PK. If ganked, skill Taunt and Decapitate to help team early and look for kills. Once PK, smoke and gank as much as possible!

Hero_Lodestone.txt_intro: Lodestone is an initiator played in the offlane due to his high survivability. Shatterstorm will drastically reduce the tankiness of any hero. Once you get your Portal Key, smoke for the enemy carry.

Hero_Magmar.txt_intro: Magmus is an initiator very flexible in role. He is commonly played as a secondary support, mid or offlaner where he roams the map and sets up kills. A portal key is essential to multi-stun/eruptions.

Hero_Maliken.txt_intro: Maliken is a carry hero that thrives on manning up at mid to low HP in order to gain bonus attack speed and magic armor. Items to remedy sustain with both attack speed and damage are key to sucess.

Hero_Martyr.txt_intro: Martyr is a defensive support hero that can play very aggressive early game with Retribution and Sol's Conviction. A well-timed storm spirit with Guardian Angel can prevent damage from a teammate.

Hero_MasterOfArms.txt_intro: Master Of Arms is a high-damage glass canon carry that can also be played as a support due to Master's Call being global. Take down stacks with acid bomb and build into damage and survivability.

Hero_Midas.txt_intro: Midas is an initiator offlane/mid hero that also works on an aggressive lane with another stunner. Split-push as often as possible and look for pick-offs with teammates around the map.

Hero_Mimix.txt_intro: Xemplar is a carry hero that can play active and look for kills with Schism. Wall of Mirrors on a target will ensure Fractal Field from illusions with hit and deal large amounts of damage quickly.

Hero_Moira.txt_intro: Moira is a support hero that can gank with her Ephemeral Forge while remaining safe from across the map. Counter-initiate  teamfights with Arcane Vortex or stop Shrunken Head + teleporting enemies.

Hero_Monarch.txt_intro: Monarch is a defensive support hero that protects your key heroes with Chrysalis, while providing map vision with Noxious Nightcrawlers. Late-game, remove stuns, sheeps etc. with Cleansing Wind.

Hero_MonkeyKing.txt_intro: Monkey King is a ganker/semi-carry hero with high mobility that can lane anywhere as a core hero, however he is preferred mid for solo exp. and rune control. Gank and farm when necessary!

Hero_Moraxus.txt_intro: Moraxus is an initiator with a powerful AOE stun in Quake and the ability to absorb target spells and projectiles with Arcane Shield. He is best played solo mid or solo offlane due to his tankiness.

Hero_Mumra.txt_intro: Pharaoh is an initiator and counter-initiator hero that locks the enemy key hero into his Wall of Mummies with himself. He can be played offlane or mid. Max hellfire in 1v1s and max E on offlane.

Hero_Nitro.txt_intro: Nitro is a fragile ranged carry that can be played in short lane or mid. Build mobility to kite your opponents from a distance and later into damage and attack speed to kill quickly.

Hero_Nomad.txt_intro: Nomad is an aggressive carry hero with high-damage output that should be played with a hit and run playstyle. A well-placed Edge Counter can devastate the enemy team. Use it well!

Hero_Oogie.txt_intro: Oogie is a magic damage carry that scales from a large mana pool. Build items according to your opponents threats to allow yourself sustain in team-fights. Oogie lacks lockdown so items are key!

Hero_Ophelia.txt_intro: Ophelia is an aggressive jungle hero that excels at ganking in the early levels using veiled rot to avoid wards. Later look to push towers with teammates to gain map control and control the game.

Hero_Panda.txt_intro: Pandamonium is a semi-carry, anti-carry initiatior that looks to lock down the enemy carry with Face Smash + Shrunken Head. Panda works best in the mid lane or a duo offlane.

Hero_Parallax.txt_intro: Parallax is a magic damage semi-carry that can be played solo mid or in the short lane farming. Building a large mana pool will make Earthshatter do huge damage to enemies with lower mana pools!

Hero_Parasite.txt_intro: Parasite is an active jungler that can roam and setup kills early on. Later you can transition from a ganker to a semi-carry. Choose between Puzzlebox + aura build or Mock + damage build.

Hero_Pearl.txt_intro: Pearl is a defensive support hero with the ability to purge buffs off enemies and debuffs from teammates with Asphyxiate. A well placed Preservation can turn a teamfight around and save allies.

Hero_Pestilence.txt_intro: Pestilence is a mobile mid/offlane hero that specializes at initiating fights with Flight and Impale. He pairs well with physical damage carries due to his Swarm debuff amplifying their damage.

Hero_Plant.txt_intro: Bramble is a tanky supportive hero that can heal allies as well as chase enemies down. Use Vine Wall to restrain enemies and stop them from fleeing, as well as push towers quickly.

Hero_PollywogPriest.txt_intro: Pollywog Priest is an initiator with great single target lockdown typically played mid lane for XP and early PK. Veiled rot to gank sidelanes and push towers with Voodoo Wards. Sotm + Resto late game.

Hero_Predator.txt_intro: Predator is a hard-carry with heavy physical damage that is great at going up against high health-pool heroes due to his Carnivorous passive. Build attack speed and damage to synergize with Terror.

Hero_Prisoner.txt_intro: Prisoner 945 is a hooking hero typically played in mid lane or an aggressive dual lane. He is great against escape-style heroes due to the restrain from Shackled. Against void talisman, buy SotM.

Hero_Prophet.txt_intro: Prophet is an aggressive support paired well with physical damage carries. Spam invigorate on your carry to boost their farm speed and keep them healed. A well-placed Shared Fate will control fights.

Hero_PuppetMaster.txt_intro: Puppet Master is a hard carry with great disables and high burst damage thanks to the combination of an Assassin's Shroud + Voodoo Puppet. Build survivability to progress in both mid and late game.

Hero_Pyromancer.txt_intro: Pyromancer is a magic damage nuker that transitions into a semi-carry with damage items thanks to Fervor. He is typically played mid lane but also works on a dual lane with a direct stun initiator.

Hero_Ra.txt_intro: Amun-Ra is an initiator/tank hero that plays in a lane (NOT in jungle). Flexible item builds allow for him to become either an offensive DPS hero or a pure front-liner utilizing 2 lives.

Hero_Rally.txt_intro: Rally is an initiator that is versatile in the laning phase being able to Compel himself and allies to safety. Acquire a SotM + PK to land big initiations and devastate the enemy team.

Hero_Rampage.txt_intro: Rampage is a roaming ganker that works well in the offlane because he is effective without much farm. Look for isolated enemies and setup ganks with teammates with Stampede + Greater Rhino.

Hero_Ravenor.txt_intro: Ravenor is a hard carry that builds up stacks on Power Overwhelming when dealing damage to enemies. High attack speed with survivability will allow you to grow charges quickly and control teamfights.

Hero_Revenant.txt_intro: Revenant is a ganker/secondary support hero that pairs well with magic damage allies. Later you can transition into a semi-carry with a Hellflower + Geobane. Roam with allies using Essence Shroud.

Hero_Rhapsody.txt_intro: Rhapsody is a defensive support hero that also works well in push lineups with her Disco Inferno AOE heal. Protective melody can prevent allies from taking damage but may require positioning items.

Hero_Riftmage.txt_intro: Riftwalker is support hero that can also work mid lane due to her ability to clear creep waves quickly and flash farm. Wormhole can be used as both initiation and counter-initiation. Position is key!

Hero_Riptide.txt_intro: Riptide is a carry hero typically played in mid lane with access to both water and rune control allowing him to gank and snowball. Build into high agility and survivability to hit hard and carry.

Hero_Rocky.txt_intro: Pebbles is an initiatior typically played in the mid lane that becomes very deadly with a Portal Key. Roam the map and setup kills with teammates, always be a threat!

Hero_Salomon.txt_intro: Salomon is a carry hero that can accumulate gold quicker than any other hero thanks to Wish for Wealth. He can be played as a shortlane farmer or as a jungler. Early large item purchases are key.

Hero_SandWraith.txt_intro: Sand Wraith is a hard carry with the ability to globally gank with Mirage and take out key targets from the opposing team. SotM will allow for a superior fear from Mirage against hard to kill targets.

Hero_Sapphire.txt_intro: Sapphire is a fragile agility carry that can burst down foes by knocking them into her Unstable Shard and attacking the shard. Crystallize can control or setup a teamfight, positioning is key!

Hero_Scar.txt_intro: The Madman is a hard carry that can be played in any lane due to his high mobility. He prefers to lane shortlane to scale quickly into late-game items and take over the game with auto-attacks.

Hero_Scout.txt_intro: Scout is a hard carry with an active playstyle that can gank due his high mobility and invisibility. Focus on farming core items in early game, then later move towards ganking with teammates.

Hero_ShadowBlade.txt_intro: Shadowblade is a hard carry that can change his main attribute with Essence Shift. Early game, focus on strength form to farm core items and eventually transition into agility form to become a carry.

Hero_Shaman.txt_intro: Demented Shaman is a support hero paired well with carries or in aggressive lanes with summoning heroes to take advantage of his healing wave for damage. Team-based items sustain team-fights!

Hero_Shellshock.txt_intro: Shellshock is a second support ganker/roamer that initiates fights with Rolling Thunder. Allies can jump into your shell and roll for extra damage and ganks. Use Fireflies to scout the enemy position.

Hero_Silhouette.txt_intro: Silhouette is a hard carry played in shortlane, able to be in 2 places at once with Shadow. Maneuver in and out of teamfights and splitpush while farming up core items to keep enemies on their toes.

Hero_SirBenzington.txt_intro: Sir Benzington is a semi-carry ganker that excels in 2v2 lanes, but can also work in the offlane or as a roamer. Knightfall can be used to gank globally with teammates. Pay close attention to the map.

Hero_Skrap.txt_intro: Skrap is a secondary support hero played in an aggressive duo lane or in solo mid. His playstyle is built around pushing towers and teamfighting, so items to compliment are key to success.

Hero_Solstice.txt_intro: Solstice is a semi-carry jungler that can both farm and gank effectively in the early game. At night time, transition into an aggressive ganker and farm jungle stacks during day time.

Hero_Soulstealer.txt_intro: Soulstealer is a carry hero that can be played both in mid or in the short lane. Obtaining a Portal Key or Assassin's Shroud will help to land a Soul Burst in teamfights. Build survivability.

Hero_Succubis.txt_intro: Succubus is a ganker typically played solo mid, but can also work as a secondary support. Mesmerize the support and Cursed Embrace the enemy key hero to control teamfights in your team's favor.

Hero_Taint.txt_intro: Gravekeeper is ganker/initiator hero played solo mid and sometimes in an aggressive duo lane. Look to use Zombie Apocalypse as often as possible either to net a kill or push a tower!

Hero_Tarot.txt_intro: Tarot is a hard carry played in the shortlane that is squishy relying on items for positioning and survivability. She can deal massive damage through her crits while stunning them with Bound by Fate.

Hero_Tempest.txt_intro: Tempest is a jungle hero that can push towers in the early game and transition into a teamfighter with Elemental Void. Acquiring a PK + Shrunken Head will help to lock down the enemy key heroes.

Hero_Treant.guide_name: WhatYouGot\'s Keeper of the Forest G
Hero_Treant.txt_intro: Keeper Of The Forest is a jungle hero that also works well in the offlane using minions to pull creeps for lane control. Push towers with teammates early on and utilize Root to control fights.

Hero_Tremble.txt_intro: Tremble is a carry with an aggressive playstyle that works both in midlane or farming in shortlane. Send mounds across the map to gank with allies using Terrorform. Farm items to scale into late game.

Hero_Tundra.txt_intro: Tundra is a ganker/initiator played mid or offlane that provides map control with shiver scouting the enemy position. Lock down the enemy key hero with Avalanche in teamfights and focus them down.

Hero_Valkyrie.txt_intro: Valkyrie is a mobile semi-carry that is best paired with another disable to land javelin. She can lane anywhere but prefers dual longlane. Use Prism to setup fights with allies mid and late game.

Hero_Vanya.txt_intro: The Dark Lady is a hard carry with the ability to silence all enemies she charges through and can slow her target of choosing. In fights, a well-placed Cover of Darkness can disrupt the enemy team.

Hero_Vindicator.txt_intro: Vindicator is a defensive support hero that specializes at disrupting opponents with silences and disarm. Final Chapter is global and can win teamfights with proper timing. Put 1 on W if vs a solo.

Hero_Voodoo.txt_intro: Voodoo Jester is an aggressive support hero that plays around cursed ground for kills. Acid cocktail works well against minion-based heroes, as the creeps get stunned for 5 seconds.

Hero_Warchief.txt_intro: Warchief is a ganking teamfight initiator that can be played mid or offlane. Warcry will drastically reduce your team Cooldowns giving you the edge in fights. Build tanky and utility for your team.

Hero_WitchSlayer.txt_intro: Witch Slayer is best played as a support hero with the ability to crowd-control the enemy. Acquire a PK to lock down the enemy and finish with Silver Bullet which becomes superior magic with SoTM.

Hero_WolfMan.txt_intro: War Beast is a carry that can both jungle and offlane by pulling creeps. Gank with Ult and push towers, farm and splitpush w/o Ult. Resto late-game to refresh SH, Puzzle and Ult. Scout with wolves.

Hero_Xalynx.txt_intro: Torturer is a heavy nuker played in midlane or as a secondary support. He is great in push or aggressive teams and building survivability will help his constant threat of AOE damage over a fight.

Hero_Yogi.txt_intro: Wildsoul is a carry hero played jungle utilizing his Swipe to flash farm and kill jungle stacks. Gank with swipe and farm core items before teamfighting and pushing towers. Solo Kong once core items.

Hero_Zephyr.txt_intro: Zephyr is a semi-carry played in shortlane or jungle that deals AOE magic damage with cyclones. Build early helm to frontline and continue into mobility and tank items allowing for damage over time.
